B-2cjMeH-opgl_B5DzQCvhvvHI6Q0" alt="Front Cover" title="Front Cover" width="128" border="1" id="summary-frontcover"></a></div><div class="bookinfo_sectionwrap"><div><a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20230706210439/https://www.google.com/search?tbo=p&amp;tbm=bks&amp;q=inauthor:%22Roshen+Dalal%22" class="secondary"><span dir="ltr">Roshen Dalal</span></a></div><div><span dir="ltr">Penguin Books India</span>, 2010 - <a class="secondary" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20230706210439/https://www.google.com/search?tbo=p&amp;tbm=bks&amp;q=subject:%22India%22&amp;source=gbs_ge_summary_r&amp;cad=0"><span dir="ltr">India</span></a> - <span dir="ltr">415 pages</span></div><div class="reviewaggregate hreview-aggregate"><a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20230706210439/https://books.google.com/books?id=pNmfdAKFpkQC&amp;sitesec=reviews" aria-label="Average user rating - Unrated"><span class="gb-star-off goog-inline-block rating"><span class="value-title" title="0.0"></span></span><span class="gb-star-off goog-inline-block"></span><span class="gb-star-off goog-inline-block"></span><span class="gb-star-off goog-inline-block"></span><span class="gb-star-off goog-inline-block"></span></a> <span class="num-ratings"><a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20230706210439/https://books.google.com/books?id=pNmfdAKFpkQC&amp;sitesec=reviews" class="sbs-count secondary"><span class="count">0</span> Reviews</a><div class="sbs-disclaimer"><span class="sbs-disclaimer-text">Reviews aren&#39;t verified, but Google checks for and removes fake content when it&#39;s identified</span></div></span></div></div><div id="synopsis"><div id="synopsis-window"><div id="synopsistext" dir="ltr" class="sa">In India, the birthplace of some of the world's major faiths and home to many more, religion is a way of life, existing as much in temples, mosques, churches and wayside shrines as it does in social laws, cultural practices and the political arena. Bringing this complex and fascinating subject into easy access through essential facts and figures, clear, concise definitions and up-to-date information on recent religio-political developments, "The Penguin Dictionary of Religion in India" is the first single-volume dictionary to provide a comprehensive account of every major religion practised in the country today. From Somnatha Temple and Babri Masjid to Golden Temple and Akali Movement; from Shariat and Eucharist to Shabbat and Nirvana; from Dalai Lama and Adi Shankaracharya to Osho and Art of Living - this meticulously researched work of reference covers a vast range of topics, placing each faith in its historical context and tracing its evolution from its inception up to the present.</div></div></div><div class="search_box_wrapper"><form action="/web/20230706210439/https://books.google.com/books" id="search_form" style="margin:0px;padding:0px;" method="get"> <input type="hidden" name="id" value="pNmfdAKFpkQC"><table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" class="swv-table"><tr><td class="swv-td-search"><span><input id="search_form_input" type="text" maxlength="1024" class="text_flat swv-input-search" aria-label="Search in this book" name="q" value="" title="Search inside" accesskey="i"></span></td><td class="swv-td-space"><div>&nbsp;</div></td><td><input type="submit" value="Search inside"></td></tr></table></form><div id="preview-link"><a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20230706210439/https://books.google.com/books?id=pNmfdAKFpkQC&amp;printsec=frontcover" class="primary"><span dir="ltr">Preview this book</span> &raquo;</a></div></div></td> </tr></table><div id="summary-second-column"></div></div></div></div></div><div class="vertical_module_list_row"><h3 class="about_title"><a name="reviews_ge_anchor"></a>What people are saying&nbsp;<span class="dash">-</span>&nbsp;<a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20230706210439/https://www.google.com/accounts/Login?service=print&amp;continue=https://books.google.com/books%3Fop%3Dlookup%26id%3DpNmfdAKFpkQC%26continue%3Dhttps://books.google.com/books%253Fid%253DpNmfdAKFpkQC%2526hl%253Den&amp;hl=en" class="primary write-review" id="write-review-link">Write a review</a></h3><div id="reviews_ge" class="about_content"><div id="reviews_ge_v"><div id="histogram-container"></div><div>We haven&#39;t found any reviews in the usual places.</div></div></div></div><div class="vertical_module_list_row"><h3 class="about_title"><a name="selected_pages_anchor"></a>Selected pages</h3><div id="selected_pages" class="about_content"><div id="selected_pages_v"><div class="selectedpagesthumbnail"><a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20230706210439/https://books.google.com/books?id=pNmfdAKFpkQC&amp;pg=PR3&amp;source=gbs_selected_pages&amp;cad=2"><img src="https://web.archive.org/web/20230706210439im_/https://books.google.com/books/content?id=pNmfdAKFpkQC&amp;pg=PR3&amp;img=1&amp;zoom=1&amp;sig=ACfU3U0zDT0lpn1QS7jQt94zvU4UbY_jAg" alt="Title Page" title="Title Page" height="160" border="1"></a><br/><a class="primary" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20230706210439/https://books.google.com/books?id=pNmfdAKFpkQC&amp;pg=PR3&amp;source=gbs_selected_pages&amp;cad=2">Title Page</a></div><div class="selectedpagesthumbnail"><a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20230706210439/https://books.google.com/books?id=pNmfdAKFpkQC&amp;pg=PA407&amp;source=gbs_selected_pages&amp;cad=2"><img src="https://web.archive.org/web/20230706210439im_/https://books.google.com/books/content?id=pNmfdAKFpkQC&amp;pg=PA407&amp;img=1&amp;zoom=1&amp;sig=ACfU3U1qmk015LDEss92zyFiKhcx0I-OOw" alt="References" title="References" height="160" border="1"></a><br/><a class="primary" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20230706210439/https://books.google.com/books?id=pNmfdAKFpkQC&amp;pg=PA407&amp;source=gbs_selected_pages&amp;cad=2">References</a></div><div style="clear:both;"></div></div></div></div><div class="vertical_module_list_row"><h3 class="about_title"><a name="toc_anchor"></a>Contents</h3><div id="toc" class="about_content"><div id="toc_v"><div class="firs